Description: Fragment of wall of a closed pottery vessel. Bands below blob rosettes, the larger one with an incised 'X'.
Curator's comments: The 'X' is probably decorative, not alphabetic.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIV, no. 608)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 673, no. 317)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.1183)
